post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Young people could use fake IDs to buy drugs, the same way they currently do with alcohol and cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Alcohol-dependent persons](https://academic.oup.com/alcalc/article/46/2/105/198339) have to face prejudices, although the substance is legal: They are often held responsible for their condition, are subject to social rejection and they are at particular risk for structural discrimination.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's not a given that the low well-being of drug users' families are a result of the drug use. The confounding variable is likely mental health issues. It's possible \\(and sometimes preferable\\) to solve the mental health issues, while not stopping the drug use."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will decrease the number of fatal overdoses by giving each user a safe dose of the drugs by regulating the drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-cocaine laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the early 1900s were directed at black men in the South.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "That's already true in [most states \\(USA\\)](https://www.ghsa.org/state-laws/issues/drug%20impaired%20driving)"}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalising the activity of drug users has negative effects on individuals, their families, and society. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Colorado has seen a "[slight increase](https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/cdphe/marijuana-use-2017)" in the number of adult marijuana users in the period 2014-2017 following legalisation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prohibition of drugs at no time endangers the personal autonomy of the individual.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "If individuals are already addicted, legalisation just means they'll be able to get their drugs more easily, so they will tend to stay addicted."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies might just as well synthesize new, less addictive and harmful drugs to meet the demand.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having drugs be both illegal and valuable has funded extensive infrastructure for smuggling things across the US border.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs will lead to people having hallucinations or becoming violent. In these instances, individuals may be a danger to themselves or others. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Or it suggests that by removing the profit motive of banned drugs, the suppliers were less motivated to produce and distribute it.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization might lead to increased consumption among children.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A high level of correlation does not indicate which of the variables is the cause and which is the effect. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Because pain is an important clinical symptom, legal recreational opioids may delay patients from seeking care in a timely fashion.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Places that have decriminalised some or all drugs have not observed a long-term increase in consumption, and occasionally even a decrease has been observed. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many constitutions and legal frameworks promote personal autonomy. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Some people may become psychologically stressed about a friend/relative coming out as gay, or an atheist as well. That doesn't mean the friend/relative did anything wrong. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It can also cause users to mix alcohol with other drugs, which [endangers users' health](https://www.northpointwashington.com/blog/dangers-mixing-alcohol-drugs/) even more."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's easier to regulate established companies in a legal market than it is in the black market. Any issue would be with bad regulations, not legalization. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help drive down the profits of drug cartels since people could get their drugs from legal reliable sources. Hence it may force the cartels to offer a purer product or less expensive to remain competitive. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Individuals who do not seek out dangerous activities shouldn't be punished for those who do. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Creativity can be stimulated through the use of drugs. Drugs could help us to live in a more creative dynamic society.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug users are detained along with violent criminals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tracing the rapist after the rape does not undo the rape itself, as the harm was already done.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, addicts would be forced to buy legally, meaning there is a record of their usage and authorities can intervene if there is an instance of drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This stress would be reduced if the drugs were legal because it would remove the threat of legal danger to any concerned person.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'True freedom of choice means that individuals must face the consequences of their actions, whether they are good or bad. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Knowledge that a friend or relative is using drugs can cause significant psychological stress to a caring or sensitive individual.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-marijuana laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war), in the Midwest and the Southwest in the 1910s and 20s, were directed at Mexican migrants and Mexican Americans.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is better to educate people on how to use valuable-yet-dangerous things safely than to ban their use entirely.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Holland, [a channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRQKXtIGcK1yEnQ4Te8hWQ) exists just to raise awareness of drugs. It explains how and when to take them, and what to do when a friend is having an OD.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It also means there will be less demand for young people as workers in the black market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, obtaining such drugs is risky, restricted and requires work. Even if they're available, making them freely available may increase the number of rape incidents."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legal sellers will be highly scrutinized and won't want to risk losing their license. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The reason for black market chemicals to be cheaper, is that the black market doesn't care about cost incurring legal restrictions and taxes. I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs have a long history of responsible use within their historical context.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, more people are addicted to work or shopping than to all illicit drugs combined \\([2010](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/)\\). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If established companies behave inappropriately with regards to the selling of drugs, people would be able to report this without fear of facing consequences for trying to buy drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Even if criminals are able to offer drugs at lower prices, people would turn to legal drugs because they would not risk prison and they would be sure of the quality of what they're buying. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "If individuals are already addicted, legalisation just means they'll be able to get their drugs more easily, so they will tend to stay addicted."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has lead to [high incarceration rates](https://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2016/jul/10/cory-booker/how-war-drugs-affected-incarceration-rates/) of otherwise inoffensive citizens. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Lack of regulation](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) has been a significant cause of the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "An Indian based study shows that substance consumption highly relate to [juvenile delinquency.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4919962/) That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There has been [no scientific consensus](https://newatlas.com/study-effects-ecstasy/10995/) on the long-term effects of ecstasy use.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Criminals are not interested in drugs, their core interest is money. To gain the largest amount of money, in the quickest time, with the least effort, is their ultimate goal. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The human right to personal autonomy](http://www.corteidh.or.cr/tablas/r26750.pdf) should include the freedom to take drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is not the government's responsibility to provide a safe place for dangerous recreational activities. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It is likely that a small group who are motivated not to take hard drugs solely because they are illegal would then try drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Profit for companies" is better than "profit for criminal cartels", if those are the two choices.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The culture of [overprescription](https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2018/06/opioid-epidemic/563576/) in the medical community has been a significant factor in the opioid crisis. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Lack of regulation](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) has been a significant cause of the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, more people are addicted to work or shopping than to all illicit drugs combined \\([2010](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/)\\). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Just because there are other systematic racial issues does not mean we cannot challenge this particular racist law.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is not the government's responsibility to provide a safe place for dangerous recreational activities. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Drug trafficking](https://www.cnbc.com/2013/08/09/Organized-crime:-Worlds-most-lucrative-criminal-activities.html?slide=1) is the most lucrative form of illicit business, worth about $2.1 trillion per year.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Strict quality controls will stimulate a fair competition amongst drug suppliers to offer the purest drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In [many countries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulation_of_nicotine_marketing), the advertisement of cigarettes and alcohol is not allowed. The same model could be adopted in the regulation of legalized drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In a free society, drug users must be free to share their perspective with others, and other people must be free to decide for themselves how they want to act.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If legalized, the users wouldn't have the same incentive to rid themselves of the evidence as quickly as possible."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This argument is prematurely claiming that the means \\(the legislation of drugs\\) is immoral. Whether it is moral or immoral should be decided after it has already happened and we can measure the impact on our society.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Specialists working for the government could provide the necessary education on the subject of responsible substance use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalised, all the ways it could harm other people could be criminalised, such as taking them before controlling dangerous machinery or smoking in public. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalising the activity of drug users has negative effects on individuals, their families, and society. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Unlike companies operating in American borders, drug cartels use violence and threats thereof to increase market share. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "In Uruguay, possession of drugs for personal use [is legal](https://www.tni.org/es/node/16660). That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is hard to determine whether the drugs actually allowed these artists to make these pieces of art or whether they just happened also to be using drugs because they had troubled minds. Sober people can be great artists. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The US government has [previously supported](https://www.ozy.com/flashback/when-the-government-said-marijuana-made-you-crazy/88232) the claim that marijuana use causes individuals to rape and murder others, or commit suicide. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This stress would be reduced if the drugs were legal because it would remove the threat of legal danger to any concerned person.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}
